144:## Suggested Build Order
145:
146:1. Spec 1 (recording & replay) — substrate for everything.
147:2. Spec 3 (synthetic playtest) — turns recording from "improve human bug reports" into "infinite autonomous bug discovery." Highest leverage.
148:3. Spec 8 (behavioral metrics) — pairs with Spec 3 to define regressions for emergent behavior.
149:4. Spec 2 (game-side annotation UI) — humans plug into the same system; game-specific work that can ship in parallel with Spec 4.
150:5. Spec 4 (standalone viewer) — productivity multiplier for both agents and humans.
151:6. Spec 7 (corpus index) — once corpus is large enough that browsing it linearly hurts.
152:7. Spec 9 (AI playtester) — once Specs 3 and 8 are mature enough to drive qualitative feedback usefully.
153:8. Spec 5 (counterfactual) — once concrete counterfactual queries emerge from agent workflows.
154:9. Spec 6 (strict-mode) — independent, can ship at any point. Schedule based on determinism-bug pain.
